{"TopicId":169020,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"How to Super-sample Your Screenshots","CreatedByName":"NumlockHolmesBR","CreatedById":183889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-29T16:39:21Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NumlockHolmesBR","CreatedById":183889,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-12-29T16:39:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEven if you have an \u003Cem\u003E1080p\u003C/em\u003E monitor you\u0027ll see that screenshots in KSP, especially after cropped, leaves a lot to be desired, and KSP\u00A0DOES have an \u0022hidden\u0022 function to help YOU out with your screenshots.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\nGo to your KSP root folder, than open the settings.cfg file\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nSearch (\u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003Ectrl\u002Bf\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E it there to help you out) for \u0022SCREENSHOT_SUPERSIZE=\u0022\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\nThe number you put in front of that statement is goin to be multiplied to your current render resolution.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\nMeaning that, if you have an 1080p resolution\u00A0(monitor)\u00A0and you put\u00A02 on the statement you are gonna have\u00A0\u003Cem\u003E4k\u003C/em\u003E screenshots, if you want an specific \u003Cem\u003E16:9 \u003C/em\u003Eresolution\u00A0or any other aspect \u003Cstrong\u003ETHAT YOU ARE RENDERING\u00A0THE GAME\u003C/strong\u003E, just use the Rule of Three:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Rule of Three Calculator\u0022 src=\u0022https://es.calcuworld.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2013/03/regla-de-tres.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooks complicated doesn\u0027t\u00A0it? But its as simple as a 5\u003Csup\u003Eth\u00A0\u003C/sup\u003Egrade multiplication an division\u00A0equation, you\u0027ll see.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA=1080 (Your resolution)\u003Cbr\u003E\nB=1 (the Super sample Statement)\u003Cbr\u003E\nX= 2160 (target resolution)\u003Cbr\u003E\ny=\u003Cstrong\u003E?\u003C/strong\u003E (target super sample statement)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nY=B . X / A\u003Cbr\u003E\nY= 1 . 2160 / 1080\u003Cbr\u003E\nY= 2160 / 1080\u003Cbr\u003E\nY=\u003Cstrong\u003E2\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo if you want a 4k screenshot while running the game at\u00A01080p just put 2 on the statement and you are good to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter all is configured just press \u003Cem\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EF1\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/em\u003E to do a in-game screenshot, and you can also press \u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cem\u003EF2\u00A0\u003C/em\u003E\u003C/strong\u003Eto hide the \u003Cem\u003EHUD\u003C/em\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHope this helps someone.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-12-29T19:43:49Z\u0022 title=\u002212/29/2017 07:43  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 29, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by NumlockHolmesBR\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nightside","CreatedById":150244,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-12T22:04:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow this is great advice- I often play on a small,\u00A0low res laptop monitor, so using this I can still create decent screen shots.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183889-numlockholmesbr/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022183889\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/183889-numlockholmesbr/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@NumlockHolmesBR\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-05-13T02:05:55Z",